	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've got a wordpress-blogg for a few years and just noticed that Wordpress seems to automatically strip old posts of their images when browsing the archive (they're still there in edit-mode).<br />It seems to shorten the posts aswell (I get a &quot;continue reading&quot; link instead of a long text).<br />I don't want any of this, but can't find anyway to configure it either. Perhaps I suck at Google, but can't find anything usefull.<br />Anyone knows what I am talking about and how to prevent it?<br /><br />Thanks alot.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
